removed.description: Jack comes upon ruins of a village and realizes it is his home.  He then reflects on the past when he was a young boy.
removed.title: XIX

removed.description: When Jack enters a spooky, old mansion and gets locked inside, he catches sight of a figure and sets after it to find out what is going on. As Jack is led further and further in, he discovers that the house and its inhabitants have an evil plan that involves…him.
removed.title: XXXV

removed.description: Jack must travel along a water creature, a mountain creature and a flying creature to get to a portal to return home. But once he reaches the portal, it is guarded by an undefeatable warrior who tells him that this portal is not for him.
removed.title: XXXII

removed.description: Jack and a Swamp Wizard travel to the four corners of the earth, collecting pieces that are meant to get Jack home. But when Aku reveals himself to be the Swamp Wizard, Jack must battle these pieces which are now being puppeteered by Aku's evil hands.
removed.title: XXXIV

removed.description: When a flatulent dragon begins stinking out an entire village.  Jack slays the beast and ventures inside it to cure to source of its bellyache.
removed.title: XXI

removed.description: Aku leads Jack to a graveyard where the dead begin to rise. An evil spirit takes over Jack's sword, leading Jack to defend himself against his own weapon. When Aku gets hold of the sword, Jack fears he's finally met his end.
removed.title: XXX

removed.description: Jack falls into a hidden temple sanctuary to find monks trained like him in the style of the Ancient Master. The Ancient Master's Son then tells Jack of a portal to send him home, but in order to use it, his new friends must be sacrificed.
removed.title: XXXVI

removed.description: Jack boards a train to his next destination only to be attacked by a couple of arguing bounty hunters.
removed.title: XXIX

removed.description: Jack is kidnapped and placed in a chain gang of warriors chosen to battle in front of a coliseum audience against the Dome of Doom's Champions.
removed.title: XVI

removed.description: Jack is carefully making his way through a labyrinth to reach a mysterious box - the problem is, so are two thieves.
removed.title: XXXIX

removed.description: Aku sends a Ninja to destroy Jack who is busily helping a port town in distress.
removed.title: XL

removed.description: Jack travels vertically up a mountain with three monks to witness the magic of the mountain only to have the power of the mountain save his very life.
removed.title: XX

removed.description: Jack comes upon a battle where a mere 300 men are fighting a vast, unending army of robots and their evil robotic leader.
removed.title: XXV

removed.description: Jack is turned into a chicken by a cranky wizard. While he tries to fix this, he gets caught by a "handler" and becomes a prize-winning Creature Combat fighter.
removed.title: XXVII

removed.description: When ancient gods try to destroy a powerful evil, they send one piece of the beast hurtling through space. This piece lands on earth, spreading its evil through the land. When it encroaches on an Emperor's empire, he takes it upon himself to destroy the evil, but ends up unleashing the evil that is Aku.
removed.title: XXXVIII

removed.description: The Scotsman needs Jack's help to save his kidnapped wife.  But this woman is hardly the distressed damsel the Scotsman makes her out to be.
removed.title: XVII

removed.description: Jack must read hieroglyphics, solve riddles and assemble a sacred scarab to call upon Ra for help in fighting evil ancient Egyptian shadow warriors.
removed.title: XXXI

removed.description: When a band of bikes mow over Jack's sandals, he goes on a hunt for the perfect footwear.
removed.title: XXVI

removed.description: Aku hires the best hunters in the galaxy to track down the most elusive of prey - Samurai Jack.
removed.title: XXII

removed.description: Aku sends out Demongo, the soul collector, to destroy Jack.  Now Jack must fight all the mighty warrior souls that Demongo has collected.
removed.title: XXIII

removed.description: An over-friendly creature begins following Jack, messing up Jack's every move along his quest.
removed.title: XXXIII

removed.description: When Jack has his sword and clothing stolen, he must give chase to a white rabbit who took them while trying to maintain his modesty.

When it encroaches on an Emperor's empire, he takes it upon himself to destroy the evil, but ends up unleashing the evil that is Aku.
